jobs_results.description:
Our client in the financial sector is seeking a techno-functional Senior Project Manager to manage end-to-end project delivery on their digital platforms.

Mandatory Skill(s)
• Degree in Computer Science/ IT or equivalent;
• At least 6 years of experience as a Project Manager;
• Strong experience in end-to-end project delivery and SDLC;
• Familiar with Adobe Experience Manager and Adobe Marketing Cloud solution;
• Excellent communication skills and ability to manage senior stakeholders;
• Good team management experience and leadership skills.

Desirable Skill(s)
• PMP-certified;
• Experience in the financial sector.

Responsibilities
• Supervise and maintain the organisation's critical application systems;
• Manage end-to-end project development and delivery, including budgeting, planning and risk evaluation;
• Coordinate development activities with cross-functional teams, including subordinates and end-users;
• Define business needs and objectives for new application system... development or for enhancements of existing systems;
• Manage and co-ordinate the activities of a team for system development, maintenance and support;
• Manage and monitor the project development and progress to ensure the project could be delivered based on agreed timeline;
• Prepare RFPs and assess proposals from vendors fairly to recommend the best solution to management;
• Manage vendors' deliverables and control the management resources;
• Ensure system development process and system output are conforming to regulation requirements and guidelines;
• Develop the department's business plan and budget, ensuring a clear alignment with the company's objectives
